  {"domain":"Science","skill":"Interpretation of Data","difficulty":"hard","type":"mc","text":"<em style=\"font-weight:400; font-size:0.85em; line-height:1.7; display:block; margin-bottom:1rem;\">Study 6: Researchers measured a river on one summer day at four sites, upstream to downstream. Dissolved oxygen (DO, mg/L) and water temperature: Site A — 12 mg/L, 14°C; Site B — 10 mg/L, 17°C; Site C — 8 mg/L, 21°C; Site D — 6 mg/L, 24°C. Trout require DO above 8 mg/L.</em>Based on the trout requirement, which sites could support trout?","choices":["A and B only","all four sites","C and D only","none of the sites"],"correct":0},
  {"domain":"Science","skill":"Scientific Investigation","difficulty":"hard","type":"mc","text":"<em style=\"font-weight:400; font-size:0.85em; line-height:1.7; display:block; margin-bottom:1rem;\">Study 6: Researchers measured a river on one summer day at four sites, upstream to downstream. Dissolved oxygen (DO, mg/L) and water temperature: Site A — 12 mg/L, 14°C; Site B — 10 mg/L, 17°C; Site C — 8 mg/L, 21°C; Site D — 6 mg/L, 24°C. Trout require DO above 8 mg/L.</em>Measuring all four sites on the same day helps ensure that","choices":["the river flows faster.","trout are present.","equipment stays dry.","weather differences between days do not confound the comparison."],"correct":3},
  {"domain":"Science","skill":"Scientific Investigation","difficulty":"hard","type":"mc","text":"<em style=\"font-weight:400; font-size:0.85em; line-height:1.7; display:block; margin-bottom:1rem;\">Study 6: Researchers measured a river on one summer day at four sites, upstream to downstream. Dissolved oxygen (DO, mg/L) and water temperature: Site A — 12 mg/L, 14°C; Site B — 10 mg/L, 17°C; Site C — 8 mg/L, 21°C; Site D — 6 mg/L, 24°C. Trout require DO above 8 mg/L.</em>To increase confidence in the results, the researchers should","choices":["round all values to whole numbers.","sample only in winter.","repeat the measurements on multiple days.","measure only one site."],"correct":2},
  {"domain":"Science","skill":"Evaluation of Models","difficulty":"hard","type":"mc","text":"<em style=\"font-weight:400; font-size:0.85em; line-height:1.7; display:block; margin-bottom:1rem;\">Study 6: Researchers measured a river on one summer day at four sites, upstream to downstream. Dissolved oxygen (DO, mg/L) and water temperature: Site A — 12 mg/L, 14°C; Site B — 10 mg/L, 17°C; Site C — 8 mg/L, 21°C; Site D — 6 mg/L, 24°C. Trout require DO above 8 mg/L.</em>The claim “warmer water holds more dissolved oxygen” is","choices":["true at Site A only.","contradicted by the data.","supported by the data.","not addressed by the data."],"correct":1}
